│ THOUGHT: The miscompile arises because VectorCombine forms a vector icmp with some lanes set to poison and then uses that vector to create a shuffle for shift amounts, propagating       │
│ poison into ashr, making the extracted lane poison even when the scalar source was defined. The fix is to avoid introducing poison for unused lanes by using undef in the built vector    │
│ and ensuring shuffle indices for irrelevant lanes are undef, preventing poison propagation. I will inspect the vector-combine implementation to adjust it to use undef instead of poison  │
│ for non-participating lanes, and then run the test harness.                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
